Shell.FM 0.4 Installation

1. Run the "reconfig" script to generate the "configure" script.
2. Run the "configure" script (e.g. './configure --prefix=/usr')
3. Build the binary ('make').
4. Install the binary ('su -c "make install-strip"').
5. Create the directories ~/.shell-fm/ and ~/.shell-fm/cache.
6. Place your configuration file in ~/.shell-fm/shell-fm.rc.
